See <a href="http://www.gutenberg-e.org/steuer/archive/detail/C11.p09.TypesofRussianPOWs.jpg.html" rel="nofollow">www.gutenberg-e.org/steuer/archive/detail/C11.p09.Typesof...</a>
for another copy of this picture, with caption as published in May 1915 and additional description:
&quot;Three types of Russian prisoners pose for this group photograph: two Bashkirian prisoners (the men with the fur caps), a Kyrgyz (who is sitting on the left with the Russian army field cap), and three Tartars (wearing the dark hats) from the Steppes of Russia. They represented the diversity of the tsarist armies fighting against the Central Powers.&quot;
